Author: Parkar
Remark: Authors took samples from wildbirds and animals, poultry chickens, rodents, humans, water, soil, and flies from poultry farms and several retail establishments. The resistance tests were not separated. Start/end dates and CLSI year were not specified.

Author: Rajkhowa
Remark: Isolates used for antibiotic resistance testing were from both diarrheic and non-diarrheic pigs. Concentrations were not given.

Author: Rasheed
Remark: 150 total samples were taken from vegetable salad, raw eggs, raw chicken, unpasteurized buffalo milk, and raw sheep meat (each 30 samples). The prevalence is calculated separately, but the resistance rates are not. Start/end dates were not given.

Author: Kalambhe
Remark: Start/end dates and guidelines were not given.

Author: Gowda
Remark: Researchers took samples from cattle carcasses, knives, cutting table surfaces, hands, air, and water at four different slaughterhouses. The prevalence was taken from only the cattle carcass samples, but the resistance rates were taken from all isolates that had S. aureus. Concentrations were not given.

Remark: Authors have have down 100 mcg of spectinomycin but 30% resistant to streptomycin in both Table 4 and the \Serotyping and in vitro antimicrobial sensitivity\ section. I'm assuming that spectinomycin is a typo. Guidelines were not given.
